plot: Claudia gets some on-the-job training in her first field assignment with Myka. But she's a bit overwhelmed by the hunky guys on the wrestling team they're investigating despite their tendency toward spontaneous human combustion. Fortunately, H. G. Wells lends a hand seeking a sympathetic, if skeptical, ear from Myka. Poor Pete, stuck back at the Warehouse, helps Artie with his infatuation with the Warehouse doctor and then takes action on his own infatuation.—David Foss
